{\rtf1\ansi\deff1\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f1\fnil \fcharset0 \cpg1252 Arial;}{\f2\fnil \fcharset0 \cpg1252 Arial;}}{\colortbl;\red0\green0\blue0;\red255\green255\blue255;\red0\green0\blue255;\red0\green0\blue255;}\plain <FCFORMSHEADER>\par <?xml version="1.0"?>\par \par <!DOCTYPE FIRSTCLASS SYSTEM "firstclass.dtd">\par \par <firstclass>\par \par \tab <fcobject objtype="oMessage" formid="141" objname="MSC-DB-031016-09 Chatrm,Embanet">\par \par \tab \tab <subject index="0" >Introducing Dennis Hamilton</subject>\par \par \tab \tab <tonames index="0" >MSC-DB-031016-09 Chatrm,Embanet</tonames>\par \par \tab \tab <tonames index="1" >MSC-DB-031016-09 Chatrm,Embanet</tonames>\par \par \tab </fcobject>\par \par </firstclass>\par \par </FCFORMSHEADER>\par \pard\f1\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\fcqt0\nosupersub\fs28\cf1\cb2\fi0\ri0\li0\ql\sb0\sl0 \par \par \f1\fs20\sl0 {\pict\dibitmap0 \picw131\pich167\piccropt-200\piccropb-200\piccropl-200\piccropr-200\wbmbitspixel16\wbmplanes1\wbmwidthbytes264 }\f1\fs28\sl0 Hello, my name is Dennis Hamilton and this is my fifth module in the M.Sc program: MSC-CS, MSC-SE, MSC-JV, MSC-WA, and now MSC-DB.  This is the photo on my Student ID card.\par \par I am 64.  I live in Seattle, Washington (on summer time, gmt-0700, until October 26), with my wife Victoria and our 3 cats.  Vicki is a master potter and teacher (\f1\fs20 {\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK "http://millennia-antica.com/"}}{\fldrslt\f1\fs28\cf4 http://millennia-antica.com}}\pard\f1\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\fcqt0\nosupersub\fs28\cf1\cb2\fi0\ri0\li0\ql\sb0\sl0 ).  We have 3 sons, all grown and unmarried.  The youngest, Yogi Japendranatha, is at the \f1\fs20 {\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK "http://www.gurudeva.dynip.com/~htoday/today/Archives/Past/2003/January/January_20_2003/"}}{\fldrslt\f1\fs28\cf4 Hindu monastery}}\pard\f1\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\fcqt0\nosupersub\fs28\cf1\cb2\fi0\ri0\li0\ql\sb0\sl0  on Kauai, Hawaii, where he is the web master, among other duties.  The oldest lives in Portland, Oregon where he is a rock musician and in a recovery program.  The middle son is a professional stage manager for local theatrical productions in Seattle.  We have 3 sisters.  The youngest works in special education in St. Cloud, Minnesota.\par \par I wrote my first computer program (in Fortran) in May of 1958 while I was working as an engineering aide at Boeing in Renton, Washington, after dropping out of college the year before.  I had already been interested in computers, and I have worked in practically all aspects of software in the time since.  Some of my experiences as a young, and then not-so-young developer are described in an on-line article, at \f1\fs20 {\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK "http://www.onlamp.com/pub/a/python/2001/04/04/se4e.html"}}{\fldrslt\f1\fs28\cf4 http://www.onlamp.com/pub/a/python/2001/04/04/se4e.html}}\pard\f1\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\fcqt0\nosupersub\fs28\cf1\cb2\fi0\ri0\li0\ql\sb0\sl0 .  \par \par By 1995 I had completed my undergraduate education with a Bachelor of Arts degree in an \f1\fs20 {\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK "http://www.excelsior.edu/"}}{\fldrslt\f1\ul\fs28\cf4 external degree program}}\pard\f1\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\fcqt0\nosupersub\fs28\cf1\cb2\fi0\ri0\li0\ql\sb0\sl0 .  (I had earned credits in computer science by taking the Graduate Record Examination in CS and challenging the major.  I then focused on philosophy, economics, and anthropology in a variety of classroom courses over the years.)\par \par My last corporate employment was at Xerox Corporation, where I worked as a software scientist and system architect of document-management systems.  I retired at the end of 1998 and I have occasional consulting projects in my semi-retirement.  The most rewarding of these include travel to Japan, where I have several colleagues.\par \par I am in this program for a serious tune up of my skills and to equip myself to teach at this level.  My desire is to pursue computer science as a scholar and as a teacher.  My intention is to excel in my participation here, and in the future beyond.\par \par The E. in my signature is for Eugene, the "\f1\fs20 {\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK "http://orcmid.com/construction/orcmid.htm"}}{\fldrslt\f1\fs28\cf4 orcmid}}\pard\f1\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\fcqt0\nosupersub\fs28\cf1\cb2\fi0\ri0\li0\ql\sb0\sl0 " in my e-mail signature is an on-line "handle" that I have used since 1979.  Compagno is the name of my lap-top computer, where I am set up for the course while I tear down my desktop system ("Centro") for upgrade to Windows XP Pro sometime during this module.  ( I said that in the last two modules.  I really have to do it now.)\par \par \par -- orcmid operating on Compagno\par -------------------------------\par Dennis E. Hamilton | on-line M.Sc in IT student | KIT eLearning\par mailto:Dennis_Hamilton@embanet.com | gsm:+1-206.779.9430\par mailto:Dennis.Hamilton@acm.org | http://orcmid.com\par OpenPGP public key fingerprint BFE5 EFB8 CB51 8781 5274  C056 D80D 0C3F A393 27EC\par \par }